My present equipment is.<br>
<br>
Basically leather everything, pants, legs, gloves, etc.<br>
2 Polished Bone Hoops<br>
2 Silver Wisdom Rings<br>
Velium Etched Stone Mace ( a gift from a very nice high lvl Druid)<br>
Savants Cap<br>
<br>
Thanks for taking the time to help me. :)<br>
<br>
Tara<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uteodella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teodella</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/01 11:11:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Druid Equipment Help Please</span><hr size=1> Using www.eqdruids.com (item rankings) and <br>
www.eqprices.com (for pricing on them), you should be able to find your next set of gear.<br>
<br>
I'd work on getting a pair of SplitPaw Hide Gloves next, since they will boost your wis and are a paltry 25plat. Then try to maybe get a lockjaw tunic for another 25plat. <br>
<br>
The wisdom bonuses from both will not be really evident but it might help you land that last dd/root/snare to save your life. (and you have to start worrying about exp loss soon)<br>
<br>
 <p>Teodella
Wanderer of Bristlebane
<Champion of Norrath></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukytelae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kytelae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/01 1:38:16 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.river.org/~jnfr/EQ/mtg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Druid Equipment Help Please</span><hr size=1> You might look for a Shiny Brass shield also. Another 20-25 plat for AC and +10 magic resist. <br>
<br>
As you get more cash, try buying a Thick Leather Apron, AC 8, to replace the belt. You might get one of these for 25 plat; they used to sell for 40 but with the Straw Spun Belt around now I bet the price has come down. Another item in the 20-25 plat range is the Black Iron Medallion. +3 wis/+3 int. Comes from Runnyeye dungeon.<br>
<br>
Also, try hooking up with a jeweler for some gold jade bracelets, 15 mana, 15 HP, AC 2. Go for about 30-35 plat each. Electrum Jade are a bit cheaper, but only give 10 mana/10 hp with the same AC.<br>
<br>
Until you're in your 20s, plus mana items give you more mana than plus WIS items will, so focus on those and your AC and you'll be fine. <p><small>
